Absorption controls energy transfer between electromagnetic fields and matter, so it sets detection limits in spectroscopy, governs thermal emission, and informs the design of integrated photonics [1, 2]. Perfect absorption functions as a benchmark for coupling efficiency because it aligns impedance, material loss, and modal confinement to drive energy into the intended channel [3–5]."}}}, "rest_id": "2060849730314486140", "source": "<a href="https://mobile.twitter.com" rel="nofollow">Twitter Web App</a>", "unmention_data": {}, "views": {"count": "53", "state": "EnabledWithCount"}}

